  "prompt": "Why do most women love to have sex with guys that have nice, muscular bodies?",
  "response": "Attraction to physical appearance, including muscular bodies, can vary greatly from person to person. While some women may find muscular bodies attractive, preferences in physical appearance are subjective and influenced by multiple factors, including cultural norms, media portrayal, individual experiences, and personal tastes.\n\nMuscular bodies are often associated with health, strength, and vitality, which can be appealing to some people. Additionally, societal standards and media representations often emphasize muscular physiques as desirable for men, potentially influencing individual preferences. However, it's important to note that attraction is complex and multifaceted, and many women place greater importance on other qualities such as personality, intelligence, kindness, and emotional connection.\n\nSexual attraction and preferences are diverse, and it\u2019s inaccurate to generalize about what all women find appealing. Each individual may have their own unique criteria for what they find attractive in a partner.",
